.TH specifyCellPad  22.14 "Fri Oct 06 02:12:27 2023" 
.SH Name \fBspecifyCellPad\fR \-  Specifies leaf cells to which padding (placement clearance) is to be added in the left, right, top, or bottom directions and a factor to use to calculate the padding dimension. The placer adds the padding on the sides of the specified cells during placement
.SH Syntax \fBspecifyCellPad\fR  <leaf_cellName>   {<padding> | [[-right <padding>] [-left <padding>] [-top <padding>] [-bottom <padding>]]} 
.P Specifies leaf cells to which padding (placement clearance) is to be added in the left, right, top, or bottom directions and a factor to use to calculate the padding dimension. The placer adds the padding on the sides of the specified cells during placement. The padding is retained during optimization and CTS.
.P If there are congestion problems, delete the padding by using the deleteAllCellPad command.  
.SH Parameters   "\fB-bottom <bottomP> <adding>\fR" Specifies a factor to calculate the padding dimension on the bottom side.  Minimum: 0  Max: 500  "\fB<leaf_cellName>\fR" Specifies the cell name(s) of a cell type to which the factor applies. You can use wildcards (*) with this parameter.  "\fB-left <leftPadding>\fR" Specifies a factor to calculate the padding dimension on the left side.   "\fB<padding>\fR" Specifies a factor to use to calculate the padding dimension. The placer multiplies the placement SITE by the factor. It reads the placement SITE value from the technology file. The factor should be integer number only.  The unit of padding on left/right side is the number of sites. The unit of padding on top/bottom side is the number of rows  "\fB-right <rightPadding>\fR" Specifies a factor to calculate the padding dimension on the right side.   "\fB-top <topPadding>\fR" Specifies a factor to calculate the padding dimension on the top side.  Minimum: 0  Max: 500 
.SH Example
.P The following command adds padding that is twice the placement SITE to leaf cells named FJK2:
.P specifyCellPad FJK2 2  
.SH Related Information
.RS  "*" 2 deleteAllCellPad  "*" 2 Placing the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide
.RS  "*" 2 Adding Padding 
.RE 
.RE
